      "tool": "task",
      "code": "{\"description\": \"Explore ProLector codebase structure\", \"prompt\": \"Explore the ProLector codebase at C:\\\\Users\\\\LLM-Test\\\\.gemini\\\\antigravity\\\\scratch\\\\prolector-yourvoice-perfected\\n\\nI need to understand:\\n1. The full src/ directory structure (all files and folders)\\n2. The main entry point and routing setup\\n3. Where the Score View page lives (the one shown at /score)\\n4. Where prosody visualization components are (ProsodyVisualizer, stress badges, coarticulation icons, pitch display)\\n5. What icon/graphics libraries are currently used\\n6. The current CSS/Tailwind setup for sizing and typography\\n\\nReturn:\\n- Full file tree of src/\\n- The key component files for Score View and prosody visualization (list their paths)\\n- What icon library is used (lucide-react? custom SVGs?)\\n- Current font sizes and sizing approach (Tailwind classes, CSS vars, etc.)\\n- Any existing accessibility features\", \"subagent_type\": \"explore\"}",
      "output": "<task id=\"ses_133849976ffeQiTZpe1PI2fI8m\" state=\"completed\">\n<task_result>\nNow I have a thorough picture of the entire codebase. Here is the complete report.\n\n---\n\n## ProLector Codebase Analysis\n\n**Base path:** `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\.gemini\\antigravity\\scratch\\prolector-yourvoice-perfected`\n\n---\n\n### 1. Full `src/` Directory Tree\n\n```\nsrc/\n├── hooks/\n│   └── use-mobile.tsx\n├── lib/\n│   ├── api/\n│   │   └── example.functions.ts\n│   ├── studio/\n│   │   ├── compute-policy.ts\n│   │   ├── demux.ts\n│   │   └── types.ts\n│   ├── teleprompter/\n│   │   ├── opfs-audio-cache.ts\n│   │   ├── prosody.ts\n│   │   ├── syllabus-mirror.ts\n│   │   ├── tokens.ts\n│   │   ├── use-recording.ts\n│   │   ├── use-syllabus-mirror.ts\n│   │   └── use-triage.ts\n│   ├── config.server.ts\n│   ├── error-capture.ts\n│   ├── error-page.ts\n│   ├── lovable-error-reporting.ts\n│   └── utils.ts\n├── components/\n│   ├── ui/\n│   │   ├── accordion.tsx\n│   │   ├── alert-dialog.tsx\n│   │   ├── alert.tsx\n│   │   ├── aspect-ratio.tsx\n│   │   ├── avatar.tsx\n│   │   ├── badge.tsx\n│   │   ├── breadcrumb.tsx\n│   │   ├── button.tsx\n│   │   ├── calendar.tsx\n│   │   ├── card.tsx\n│   │   ├── carousel.tsx\n│   │   ├── chart.tsx\n│   │   ├── checkbox.tsx\n│   │   ├── collapsible.tsx\n│   │   ├── command.tsx\n│   │   ├── context-menu.tsx\n│   │   ├── dialog.tsx\n│   │   ├── drawer.tsx\n│   │   ├── dropdown-menu.tsx\n│   │   ├── form.tsx\n│   │   ├── hover-card.tsx\n│   │   ├── input-otp.tsx\n│   │   ├── input.tsx\n│   │   ├── label.tsx\n│   │   ├── menubar.tsx\n│   │   ├── navigation-menu.tsx\n│   │   ├── pagination.tsx\n│   │   ├── popover.tsx\n│   │   ├── progress.tsx\n│   │   ├── radio-group.tsx\n│   │   ├── resizable.tsx\n│   │   ├── scroll-area.tsx\n│   │   ├── select.tsx\n│   │   ├── separator.tsx\n│   │   ├── sheet.tsx\n│   │   ├── sidebar.tsx\n│   │   ├── skeleton.tsx\n│   │   ├── slider.tsx\n│   │   ├── sonner.tsx\n│   │   ├── switch.tsx\n│   │   ├── table.tsx\n│   │   ├── tabs.tsx\n│   │   ├── textarea.tsx\n│   │   ├── toggle-group.tsx\n│   │   ├── toggle.tsx\n│   │   └── tooltip.tsx\n│   ├── teleprompter/\n│   │   ├── ABContrast.tsx\n│   │   ├── Coachmark.tsx\n│   │   ├── EngineStatus.tsx\n│   │   ├── PitchContour.tsx\n│   │   ├── ProsodyVisualizer.tsx\n│   │   ├── PunchInEditor.tsx\n│   │   ├── StumblePlaylist.tsx\n│   │   ├── TranscriptEditor.tsx\n│   │   └── TranscriptStage.tsx\n│   ├── studio/\n│   │   ├── ClipEditor.tsx\n│   │   ├── ComputeHud.tsx\n│   │   ├── Dropzone.tsx\n│   │   ├── EdlArticle.tsx\n│   │   ├── Filmstrip.tsx\n│   │   └── VideoFrameLayer.tsx\n│   ├── SiteFooter.tsx\n│   └── SiteNav.tsx\n├── routes/\n│   ├── __root.tsx\n│   ├── index.tsx\n│   ├── about.tsx\n│   ├── git.tsx\n│   ├── score.tsx\n│   ├── studio.tsx\n│   ├── teleprompter.tsx\n│   └── README.md\n├── routeTree.gen.ts\n├── router.tsx\n├── server.ts\n├── start.ts\n├── styles.css\n└── main.tsx (entry, implied by TanStack Start)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Main Entry Point and Routing Setup\n\n| Concern | File |\n|---|---|\n| TanStack Start bootstrap | `src/start.ts` |\n| SSR error wrapper | `src/server.ts` |\n| Router factory (`createRouter`) | `src/router.tsx` |\n| Auto-generated route tree | `src/routeTree.gen.ts` |\n| Root layout (shell, providers, `<Outlet />`) | `src/routes/__root.tsx` |\n\n**Framework:** TanStack Router (file-based) with TanStack Start (SSR). The root layout wraps everything in `QueryClientProvider` + `TooltipProvider`. The HTML shell is dark-only (`<html className=\"dark\">`).\n\n**Routes defined:**\n| Path | File |\n|---|---|\n| `/` | `src/routes/index.tsx` |\n| `/about` | `src/routes/about.tsx` |\n| `/score` | `src/routes/score.tsx` |\n| `/studio` | `src/routes/studio.tsx` |\n| `/git` | `src/routes/git.tsx` |\n| `/teleprompter` | `src/routes/teleprompter.tsx` |\n\n---\n\n### 3. Score View Page (`/score`)\n\n**Primary file:** `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\.gemini\\antigravity\\scratch\\prolector-yourvoice-perfected\\src\\routes\\score.tsx`\n\nThis is a self-contained page component (`ScoreView`) that:\n\n- Accepts a script text + WPM setting\n- Tokenizes the script via `src/lib/teleprompter/tokens.ts`\n- Computes prosody (stress, vowel compression, coarticulation, F0 pitch) via `src/lib/teleprompter/prosody.ts`\n- Groups tokens by sentence\n- Renders each sentence inside a `<PitchContour>` component\n- Includes a toolbar with Play/Pause, Reset, WPM slider, WPM presets (TED Talk, Tutorial, BBC News, Audiobook, Conversational), Zoom slider, and an Annotations toggle\n- Has keyboard shortcuts: Space (play/pause), R (reset), Arrow Up/Down (WPM +/-5)\n- Has a color-coded legend for stress dots, vowel compression bars, and coarticulation symbols\n\n**Supporting files consumed by Score View:**\n\n| File | Role |\n|---|---|\n| `src/lib/teleprompter/tokens.ts` | Tokenizer, sentence grouping, `findTokenAtMs`, WPM math |\n| `src/lib/teleprompter/prosody.ts` | `estimateStress`, `estimateVowelCompression`, `detectCoarticulation`, `isContentWord` |\n| `src/components/teleprompter/PitchContour.tsx` | The actual rendered visualization per sentence |\n| `src/components/teleprompter/ProsodyVisualizer.tsx` | Per-token prosody overlay (used within teleprompter, not directly in score.tsx) |\n\n---\n\n### 4. Prosody Visualization Components\n\n#### PitchContour (primary visualization used in Score View)\n**Path:** `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\.gemini\\antigravity\\scratch\\prolector-yourvoice-perfected\\src\\components\\teleprompter\\PitchContour.tsx`\n\nRenders:\n- **Continuous SVG pitch contour** (smooth bezier curve of F0 Hz across all words in a sentence, with a filled area under the curve)\n- **Pitch dots** at each word's nucleus frequency, with Hz labels\n- **Text layer** below the SVG with clickable words\n- **Stress badges** (dot symbols above each word: `●` primary, `○` secondary, `·` unstressed)\n- **Coarticulation icons** (positioned at top-right of words: `→r` linking-r, `ɾ` flap-t, `↻` intrusion, `⊘` elision, `≈` assimilation)\n- **Vowel compression bars** (colored horizontal bar beneath each word: green=full, yellow=compressed, orange=reduced, red=schwa)\n- Active word highlighting during playback\n\nProps: `words`, `prosodyMap`, `charWidth` (default 9), `contourHeight` (default 80), `showAnnotations`, `currentMs`, `onWordClick`.\n\n#### ProsodyVisualizer (per-token overlay, used in teleprompter mode)\n**Path:** `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\.gemini\\antigravity\\scratch\\prolector-yourvoice-perfected\\src\\components\\teleprompter\\ProsodyVisualizer.tsx`\n\nRenders per-token:\n- **Stress indicator** (above the word, same dot symbols)\n- **Pitch sparkline** (mini SVG bezier curve, the `PitchSparkline` sub-component, using Hz normalization 80-300 Hz range)\n- **Vowel compression badge** (below, percentage or schwa symbol)\n- **Coarticulation badge** (`CoarticulationBadge` sub-component with Unicode symbols and native `title` tooltips)\n\n#### Prosody data model\n**Path:** `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\.gemini\\antigravity\\scratch\\prolector-yourvoice-perfected\\src\\lib\\teleprompter\\prosody.ts`\n\nTypes: `ProsodyWord`, `ProsodySentence`, `StressLevel`, `CoarticulationType`.\nFunctions: `detectCoarticulation`, `estimateStress`, `estimateSyllableCount`, `estimateVowelCompression`, `isContentWord`.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Icon/Graphics Libraries\n\n**lucide-react** (v0.575.0) is the sole icon library. It is used exclusively inside the `src/components/ui/` shadcn/ui component library (18 files import from it). Icons used include: `Check`, `ChevronDown`, `ChevronLeft`, `ChevronRight`, `ChevronRight`, `Circle`, `GripVertical`, `Minus`, `MoreHorizontal`, `PanelLeft`, `Search`, `X`, `ArrowLeft`, `ArrowRight`, `ChevronDownIcon`, `ChevronLeftIcon`, `ChevronRightIcon`.\n\n**No custom SVG icon files exist.** The prosody visualization uses **inline SVG elements** (hand-drawn bezier paths in `PitchContour.tsx` and `ProsodyVisualizer.tsx`) and **Unicode text symbols** for all prosody icons:\n- Stress: `●` / `○` / `·`\n- Coarticulation: `→r`, `↻`, `⊘`, `≈`, `ɾ`, `ʔ`\n- Vowel compression: colored bars + percentage text or `ə`\n\nThe `components.json` confirms: `\"iconLibrary\": \"lucide\"`.\n\n---\n\n### 6. CSS / Tailwind Setup for Sizing and Typography\n\n**CSS framework:** Tailwind CSS v4.2.1 with the `@tailwindcss/vite` plugin. Uses `tw-animate-css` for animation utilities. The `class-variance-authority` (cva) + `tailwind-merge` + `clsx` pattern is used for component variants.\n\n**Theme tokens** (defined in `src/styles.css` via `@theme inline`):\n\n| Token | Value |\n|---|---|\n| `--font-sans` | `'Inter', ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif` |\n| `--font-display` | `'Inter Tight', 'Inter', sans-serif` |\n| `--font-mono` | `'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, monospace` |\n\n**Color palette** (dark-only, oklch):\n- Background: `oklch(0.145 0 0)` (#09090b)\n- Foreground: `oklch(0.985 0 0)` (#fafafa)\n- Primary: `oklch(0.705 0.213 47.604)` (#f97316 orange)\n- Muted foreground: `oklch(0.708 0 0)` (#71717a)\n- Border: `oklch(0.269 0 0)` (#27272a)\n\n**Font sizes used throughout the codebase** (Tailwind classes and inline styles):\n\n| Context | Size |\n|---|---|\n| Hero headline (`text-5xl md:text-7xl`) | ~3rem / 4.5rem |\n| Section headings (`text-3xl md:text-4xl`, `text-xl`) | 1.875rem / 2.25rem / 1.25rem |\n| Brand name (`text-lg`, `text-xl`) | 1.125rem / 1.25rem |\n| Body text (`text-sm`, `text-base`) | 0.875rem / 1rem |\n| Labels / nav (`text-xs`) | 0.75rem |\n| Micro labels (`text-[10px]`, `text-[11px]`) | 10px / 11px |\n| Tiny annotations (`text-[9px]`, `text-[8px]`, `text-[7px]`, `text-[6px]`) | 9px / 8px / 7px / 6px |\n| Score text layer (inline `fontSize: 28`) | 28px fixed |\n| ProsodyVisualizer stress dots (`text-[8px]`, scaled) | 8px base, scaled by `fontSize/52` |\n| ProsodyVisualizer vowel badges (`text-[6px]`, scaled) | 6px base, scaled |\n| Coarticulation badges (`text-[7px]`, scaled) | 7px base, scaled |\n| PitchContour stress dots (`text-[7px]`) | 7px |\n| PitchContour coartic icons (`text-[6px]`) | 6px |\n| PitchContour Hz labels (SVG `fontSize={9}`) | 9px |\n\n**Sizing approach:** Predominantly Tailwind utility classes (`text-*`, `h-*`, `w-*`, `px-*`, `py-*`, `gap-*`, `max-w-7xl`, etc.) with occasional inline styles for dynamic/computed values. The `ProsodyVisualizer` uses a `scale` factor (`Math.max(0.4, Math.min(1, fontSize / 52))`) to proportionally scale all annotation elements. The `PitchContour` uses a `charWidth` prop (default 9px) as the fundamental horizontal unit. No CSS custom properties are used for font sizes -- all sizing is Tailwind classes or inline `style={{ fontSize: ... }}`.\n\n**Custom animations** (in `styles.css`):\n- `animate-fade-up`: fade + translateY entrance\n- `animate-scroll`: infinite vertical scroll (teleprompter mockup)\n\n**Body defaults** (in `@layer base`):\n```css\nbody {\n  background-color: var(--color-background);\n  color: var(--color-foreground);\n  font-family: var(--font-sans);\n  font-feature-settings: \"ss01\", \"cv11\";\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. Existing Accessibility Features\n\n**In the shadcn/ui component library (systematic, inherited):**\n- `focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-1/2 focus-visible:ring-ring` on all interactive elements (button, input, checkbox, switch, slider, tabs, toggle, etc.)\n- `sr-only` spans for screen-reader-only text (sidebar toggle, sheet close, carousel prev/next, pagination)\n- `aria-label` on pagination buttons, sidebar toggle, engine status toggles\n- `aria-current=\"page\"` on active pagination items\n- `aria-hidden=\"true\"` on decorative elements\n- `aria-disabled` on disabled sidebar menu items\n- `aria-describedby` / `aria-invalid` on form fields\n- `role=\"navigation\"` on pagination, `role=\"separator\"` on OTP input, `role=\"region\"` + `aria-roledescription=\"carousel\"` on carousels\n- Radix UI primitives handle most ARIA semantics automatically (dialog, tabs, accordion, popover, tooltip, etc.)\n\n**In the Score View page:**\n- Keyboard shortcuts: Space (play/pause), R (reset), Arrow Up/Down (WPM) -- with guard to skip when focused on textarea/input\n- Words are clickable (click to scrub playhead)\n- Coarticulation badges have native HTML `title` attributes for tooltip on hover\n- WPM slider and zoom slider use native `<input type=\"range\">`\n- Annotations toggle checkbox\n\n**Gaps / things NOT present:**\n- No `aria-label` or `role` attributes on the SVG pitch contour or its interactive word elements in `PitchContour.tsx`\n- The ProsodyVisualizer Unicode symbols (stress dots, coarticulation icons) have no screen-reader text -- they are purely visual\n- No `aria-live` regions for playback state changes\n- The legend in Score View is purely visual (no `aria-label` on the legend container)\n- No skip-to-content link\n- The `Coachmark` overlay has no `role=\"dialog\"` or focus trapping\n</task_result>\n</task>",
