      "text": "The user is looking at the teleprompter page (/teleprompter) and wants a floating mini player that stays visible when scrolling, with auto-collapse behavior when not interacting. Let me look at the teleprompter page to understand its current structure, then build the floating mini control.\n\nActually, wait - the user was just on /score and now they're on /teleprompter. They want this floating mini player on the score page specifically (since that's what we were working on). Let me re-read their message: \"as i scroll i should be able to still play pause etc even if its sth small floating in the cornet and if im noit interacting with it it further closes on itself.\"\n\n\nSo they want a small floating widget in the corner that auto-collapses when idle, but the screenshot shows the teleprompter page - I'm not sure if they're showing me an example or if they want this feature there too. I'll build it for the score page since that's where we've been working, and the implementation approach would be similar for the teleprompter if needed.\n\nI'm creating a FloatingPlayer component that starts as a minimal circle with play/pause controls, expands on hover to reveal additional buttons like reset and WPM adjustment, and auto-collapses after a few seconds of inactivity. It stays fixed in the bottom-right corner so it's always accessible.",
      "timestamp": 1781547838955
